{"body":"[{\"data\":1,\"prerenderedAt\":687},[\"ShallowReactive\",2],{\"navigation\":3,\"index\":26,\"index-blogs\":171,\"mdc--bnud8k-key\":657,\"mdc--xfoigd-key\":669,\"mdc-9lez36-key\":678},[4],{\"title\":5,\"path\":6,\"stem\":7,\"children\":8,\"page\":25},\"Blog\",\"/blog\",\"blog\",[9,13,17,21],{\"title\":10,\"path\":11,\"stem\":12},\"From Mockup to Market: My End-to-End Product Design Process\",\"/blog/from-mockup-to-market\",\"blog/from-mockup-to-market\",{\"title\":14,\"path\":15,\"stem\":16},\"How I Built My Design System from Scratch\",\"/blog/how-i-built-my-own-design-system-from-scratch\",\"blog/how-i-built-my-own-design-system-from-scratch\",{\"title\":18,\"path\":19,\"stem\":20},\"The Psychology of Color in UI Design\",\"/blog/psychology-of-color-in-ui-design\",\"blog/psychology-of-color-in-ui-design\",{\"title\":22,\"path\":23,\"stem\":24},\"The Case for Slow Design in a Fast-Paced Digital World\",\"/blog/slow-design-in-fast-paced-digital-world\",\"blog/slow-design-in-fast-paced-digital-world\",false,{\"id\":27,\"title\":28,\"about\":29,\"blog\":32,\"body\":35,\"description\":36,\"experience\":37,\"extension\":64,\"faq\":65,\"hero\":104,\"meta\":138,\"navigation\":139,\"path\":140,\"seo\":141,\"stem\":144,\"testimonials\":145,\"__hash__\":170},\"index/index.yml\",\"Hey, I'm Emma Thompson UX/UI Designer\",{\"title\":30,\"description\":31},\"About Me\",\"As a UX/UI designer and front-end developer with 6 years of experience, I leverage my Boston University Interactive Design degree to craft user-centered digital experiences.\\nMy approach blends creative strategy with technical expertise, transforming concepts into functional, purposeful digital products that seamlessly integrate design and technology.\\n\",{\"title\":33,\"description\":34},\"Latest Articles\",\"Some of my recent thoughts\",null,\"I craft intuitive digital experiences where design meets functionality. Based in Boston, bringing ideas to life through code and creativity.\",{\"title\":38,\"items\":39},\"Work Experience\",[40,48,56],{\"position\":41,\"date\":42,\"company\":43},\"Brand Designer at\",\"2023 - Present\",{\"name\":44,\"logo\":45,\"url\":46,\"color\":47},\"Nuxt\",\"i-simple-icons-nuxtdotjs\",\"https://nuxt.com\",\"#00DC82\",{\"position\":49,\"date\":50,\"company\":51},\"Assets Designer at\",\"2022 - 2023\",{\"name\":52,\"logo\":53,\"url\":54,\"color\":55},\"Raycast\",\"i-simple-icons-raycast\",\"https://raycast.com\",\"#FF6363\",{\"position\":57,\"date\":58,\"company\":59},\"Senior UX/UI Designer at\",\"2020 - 2021\",{\"name\":60,\"logo\":61,\"url\":62,\"color\":63},\"Linear\",\"i-simple-icons-linear\",\"https://linear.app\",\"#5E6AD2\",\"yml\",{\"title\":66,\"description\":67,\"categories\":68},\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"Answers to common questions about my process and services.\",[69,81,96],{\"title\":70,\"questions\":71},\"Services & Process\",[72,75,78],{\"label\":73,\"content\":74},\"What services do you offer?\",\"I specialize in UX/UI design and front-end development. This includes user research, wireframing, interactive prototyping, creating intuitive user interfaces, building responsive websites and web applications (especially with Vue.js/Nuxt.js), and developing design systems. My goal is to create seamless digital experiences from concept to deployment.\\n\",{\"label\":76,\"content\":77},\"What is your design process like?\",\"My process is collaborative and iterative, typically involving stages like Discovery & Research, Ideation & Prototyping, User Testing, Visual Design, and close collaboration with development teams during implementation. I tailor the process based on project needs, always focusing on user-centered solutions.\\n\",{\"label\":79,\"content\":80},\"Do you work with startups?\",\"Absolutely! I enjoy working with startups to help shape their product vision and create user-friendly interfaces from the ground up. I can adapt my process to fit the fast-paced startup environment.\\n\",{\"title\":82,\"questions\":83},\"Pricing & Timelines\",[84,87,90,93],{\"label\":85,\"content\":86},\"How much does a project typically cost?\",\"Project costs vary based on scope, complexity, features, and timeline. For comprehensive UX/UI design and front-end development projects, my engagements typically start around $5,000, with average projects ranging between $8,000 and $25,000. For consulting or specific design tasks, my day rate is $700.\\n\",{\"label\":88,\"content\":89},\"What are your payment terms?\",\"I generally require a 40% deposit to schedule the project and begin work, with the remaining 60% due upon successful project completion and delivery. I accept payments via bank transfer and Stripe.\\n\",{\"label\":91,\"content\":92},\"How long does a typical project take?\",\"Timelines depend heavily on the project's scope and complexity. Smaller projects might take 3-4 weeks, while larger, more involved projects can range from 2 to 4 months. I always provide a detailed timeline estimate after the initial discovery phase.\\n\",{\"label\":94,\"content\":95},\"Do you offer retainers or ongoing support?\",\"Yes, for clients needing ongoing design support, feature development, or maintenance, I offer monthly retainer options tailored to specific needs. Let's discuss if this is something you're interested in.\\n\",{\"title\":30,\"questions\":97},[98,101],{\"label\":99,\"content\":100},\"What do you enjoy most about your work?\",\"I love the challenge of solving complex problems through design and technology. It's incredibly rewarding to see people interact with something I've created and find it genuinely useful and easy to navigate. Bridging the gap between user needs and technical possibilities is what truly excites me.\\n\",{\"label\":102,\"content\":103},\"What are your hobbies outside of work?\",\"When I'm not designing or coding, I enjoy exploring Boston's neighborhoods, trying out new coffee shops, and hiking in the nearby reservations. I'm also passionate about photography and occasionally contribute to open-source projects.\\n\",{\"links\":105,\"images\":110},[106],{\"label\":107,\"to\":108,\"color\":109},\"Use this template\",\"https://github.com/nuxt-ui-templates/portfolio\",\"neutral\",[111,114,117,120,123,126,129,132,135],{\"src\":112,\"alt\":113},\"/hero/random-1.avif\",\"Random Image 1\",{\"src\":115,\"alt\":116},\"/hero/random-2.avif\",\"Random Image 2\",{\"src\":118,\"alt\":119},\"/hero/random-3.avif\",\"Random Image 3\",{\"src\":121,\"alt\":122},\"/hero/random-4.avif\",\"Random Image 4\",{\"src\":124,\"alt\":125},\"/hero/random-5.avif\",\"Random Image 5\",{\"src\":127,\"alt\":128},\"/hero/random-6.avif\",\"Random Image 6\",{\"src\":130,\"alt\":131},\"/hero/random-7.avif\",\"Random Image 7\",{\"src\":133,\"alt\":134},\"/hero/random-8.avif\",\"Random Image 8\",{\"src\":136,\"alt\":137},\"/hero/random-9.avif\",\"Random Image 9\",{},true,\"/\",{\"title\":142,\"description\":143},\"Emma Thompson - UX/UI Designer\",\"Welcome to my portfolio! I'm Emma Thompson, a UX/UI designer and front-end developer based in Boston. I specialize in creating user-centered digital experiences that are both beautiful and functional.\",\"index\",[146,154,162],{\"quote\":147,\"author\":148},\"Emma's approach to UX design completely transformed our product. She has a rare ability to balance beautiful aesthetics with functional simplicity. The redesign not only looked better, but it reduced our customer support tickets by 40% and increased conversion rates across all key metrics.\",{\"name\":149,\"description\":150,\"avatar\":151},\"Sarah Chen\",\"Product Director at Bloom Finance\",{\"src\":152,\"srcset\":153},\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1487412720507-e7ab37603c6f?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=40&h=40&q=80\",\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1487412720507-e7ab37603c6f?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=80&h=80&q=80 2x\",{\"quote\":155,\"author\":156},\"Working with Emma was the best decision we made for our startup. She didn't just deliver designs—she challenged our assumptions, conducted thorough user research, and created an experience that truly resonated with our audience. Her technical knowledge of front-end development meant the handoff to our engineering team was seamless.\",{\"name\":157,\"description\":158,\"avatar\":159},\"Michael Rodriguez\",\"Co-founder of Wavelength Music\",{\"src\":160,\"srcset\":161},\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472099645785-5658abf4ff4e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=40&h=40&q=80\",\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472099645785-5658abf4ff4e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=80&h=80&q=80 2x\",{\"quote\":163,\"author\":164},\"Emma stands out in her ability to translate complex sustainability data into intuitive interfaces. Her work on EcoTrack wasn't just visually stunning—it fundamentally changed how our users interact with environmental information. She approaches each problem with both creativity and analytical rigor, which is exactly what we needed.\",{\"name\":165,\"description\":166,\"avatar\":167},\"Dr. Aisha Johnson\",\"Chief Innovation Officer at GreenTech Solutions\",{\"src\":168,\"srcset\":169},\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573497019940-1c28c88b4f3e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=40&h=40&q=80\",\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573497019940-1c28c88b4f3e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=2&w=80&h=80&q=80 2x\",\"kqe_5qOsnVSKUhyGPrPx9Pwdv-xQH_022qDWxuWE8Fo\",[172,554,607],{\"id\":173,\"title\":10,\"author\":174,\"body\":178,\"date\":546,\"description\":547,\"extension\":548,\"image\":549,\"meta\":550,\"minRead\":551,\"navigation\":139,\"path\":11,\"seo\":552,\"stem\":12,\"__hash__\":553},\"blog/blog/from-mockup-to-market.md\",{\"name\":175,\"avatar\":176},\"Emma Thompson\",{\"src\":177,\"alt\":175},\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1701615004837-40d8573b6652?q=80&w=1480&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D\",{\"type\":179,\"value\":180,\"toc\":513},\"minimark\",[181,185,188,193,196,201,204,210,214,217,221,224,237,241,244,248,251,255,258,286,290,293,319,323,326,330,333,337,340,351,355,358,369,373,376,387,391,394,398,401,415,419,422,436,440,443,447,450,454,457,461,464,468,471,482,486,489,500,503,507,510],[182,183,184],\"p\",{},\"Creating successful digital products isn't about following a rigid formula—it's about developing a flexible framework that adapts to the unique challenges of each project. After refining my approach across dozens of products, I've developed a process that consistently delivers results while leaving room for creativity and iteration.\",[182,186,187],{},\"In this article, I'll walk through my end-to-end design process, from initial discovery to developer handoff, using my recent work on the EcoTrack application as a case study.\",[189,190,192],\"h2\",{\"id\":191},\"phase-1-discovery-research\",\"Phase 1: Discovery & Research\",[182,194,195],{},\"Every great product starts with understanding the problem it's trying to solve. For EcoTrack, our challenge was creating an engaging way for users to track their environmental impact without feeling overwhelmed by guilt or complex data.\",[197,198,200],\"h3\",{\"id\":199},\"user-interviews\",\"User Interviews\",[182,202,203],{},\"I began by conducting interviews with 12 potential users across different demographics, focusing on their current habits and attitudes toward sustainability. These conversations revealed a crucial insight: most people wanted to make environmentally friendly choices but felt paralyzed by the complexity of calculating their impact.\",[205,206,207],\"blockquote\",{},[182,208,209],{},\"\\\"I care about the environment, but I have no idea if using a paper bag is actually better than plastic, or if my reusable water bottle makes any difference.\\\" — Interview participant\",[197,211,213],{\"id\":212},\"competitive-analysis\",\"Competitive Analysis\",[182,215,216],{},\"Next, I analyzed existing sustainability apps, creating a feature comparison matrix to identify gaps and opportunities. Most competitors focused on carbon footprint calculations but failed to provide actionable guidance or positive reinforcement.\",[197,218,220],{\"id\":219},\"defining-success\",\"Defining Success\",[182,222,223],{},\"Before opening Figma, I collaborated with stakeholders to define clear success metrics:\",[225,226,227,231,234],\"ul\",{},[228,229,230],\"li\",{},\"Increase daily active usage by 40%\",[228,232,233],{},\"Improve user-reported understanding of environmental impact\",[228,235,236],{},\"Drive measurable behavior changes in at least two sustainability categories\",[189,238,240],{\"id\":239},\"phase-2-ideation-conceptualization\",\"Phase 2: Ideation & Conceptualization\",[182,242,243],{},\"With a solid understanding of the problem space, I moved into the creative phase of the process.\",[197,245,247],{\"id\":246},\"sketching\",\"Sketching\",[182,249,250],{},\"I always start with pen and paper, rapidly exploring different approaches without the constraints of digital tools. For EcoTrack, I filled three sketchbooks with concepts ranging from gamified experiences to data-heavy dashboards.\",[197,252,254],{\"id\":253},\"information-architecture\",\"Information Architecture\",[182,256,257],{},\"Based on research insights, I developed a user-centered information architecture that prioritized simplicity and actionable information:\",[259,260,261,268,274,280],\"ol\",{},[228,262,263,267],{},[264,265,266],\"strong\",{},\"Dashboard\",\" — Personalized overview with immediate impact insights\",[228,269,270,273],{},[264,271,272],{},\"Daily Tracker\",\" — Simple logging of activities with immediate feedback\",[228,275,276,279],{},[264,277,278],{},\"Impact Journey\",\" — Visualization of progress over time\",[228,281,282,285],{},[264,283,284],{},\"Action Center\",\" — Customized recommendations based on user behavior\",[197,287,289],{\"id\":288},\"design-principles\",\"Design Principles\",[182,291,292],{},\"I established four core design principles to guide all decisions:\",[225,294,295,301,307,313],{},[228,296,297,300],{},[264,298,299],{},\"Simplify complexity\",\" — Translate environmental impact into understandable units\",[228,302,303,306],{},[264,304,305],{},\"Celebrate progress\",\" — Focus on positive reinforcement rather than guilt\",[228,308,309,312],{},[264,310,311],{},\"Enable informed choices\",\" — Provide context for decision-making\",[228,314,315,318],{},[264,316,317],{},\"Design for habit formation\",\" — Create satisfying interaction loops\",[189,320,322],{\"id\":321},\"phase-3-prototyping-testing\",\"Phase 3: Prototyping & Testing\",[182,324,325],{},\"With the conceptual framework in place, I moved into the iterative cycle of prototyping and testing.\",[197,327,329],{\"id\":328},\"low-fidelity-wireframes\",\"Low-Fidelity Wireframes\",[182,331,332],{},\"I created wireframes focusing on user flows and information hierarchy, deliberately keeping the visual design minimal to focus feedback on functionality and structure.\",[197,334,336],{\"id\":335},\"user-testing-round-1\",\"User Testing (Round 1)\",[182,338,339],{},\"Testing wireframes with 8 participants revealed several key insights:\",[225,341,342,345,348],{},[228,343,344],{},\"Users wanted more immediate feedback when logging activities\",[228,346,347],{},\"The impact visualization wasn't intuitive for most users\",[228,349,350],{},\"People were confused by technical environmental terminology\",[197,352,354],{\"id\":353},\"mid-fidelity-prototypes\",\"Mid-Fidelity Prototypes\",[182,356,357],{},\"Based on testing feedback, I refined the concept and developed interactive prototypes with more visual detail, focusing on:\",[225,359,360,363,366],{},[228,361,362],{},\"Simplified data visualization using familiar metaphors\",[228,364,365],{},\"Immediate positive reinforcement for logged activities\",[228,367,368],{},\"Progressive disclosure of more complex environmental information\",[197,370,372],{\"id\":371},\"user-testing-round-2\",\"User Testing (Round 2)\",[182,374,375],{},\"A second round of testing showed significant improvements in usability, but highlighted new challenges:\",[225,377,378,381,384],{},[228,379,380],{},\"Users wanted to compare their impact with friends or community averages\",[228,382,383],{},\"Weekly summaries were more motivating than daily statistics\",[228,385,386],{},\"The onboarding process felt too lengthy\",[189,388,390],{\"id\":389},\"phase-4-visual-design-refinement\",\"Phase 4: Visual Design & Refinement\",[182,392,393],{},\"With the core experience validated, I moved into high-fidelity visual design.\",[197,395,397],{\"id\":396},\"visual-language\",\"Visual Language\",[182,399,400],{},\"I developed a visual language that balanced approachability with credibility:\",[225,402,403,406,409,412],{},[228,404,405],{},\"A nature-inspired color palette with clear functional color coding\",[228,407,408],{},\"Custom iconography that simplified complex concepts\",[228,410,411],{},\"Typography that prioritized readability across devices\",[228,413,414],{},\"Micro-interactions that provided satisfaction and reinforcement\",[197,416,418],{\"id\":417},\"design-system\",\"Design System\",[182,420,421],{},\"To ensure consistency and facilitate development, I created a comprehensive design system including:\",[225,423,424,427,430,433],{},[228,425,426],{},\"Component library with documented states and behaviors\",[228,428,429],{},\"Responsive layout guidelines\",[228,431,432],{},\"Animation specifications\",[228,434,435],{},\"Accessibility standards\",[197,437,439],{\"id\":438},\"final-prototype\",\"Final Prototype\",[182,441,442],{},\"The final prototype brought together all elements into a cohesive experience, which we tested with a broader user group before moving to development.\",[189,444,446],{\"id\":445},\"phase-5-implementation-iteration\",\"Phase 5: Implementation & Iteration\",[182,448,449],{},\"The design process doesn't end when development begins—it evolves.\",[197,451,453],{\"id\":452},\"developer-collaboration\",\"Developer Collaboration\",[182,455,456],{},\"I worked closely with developers throughout implementation, participating in code reviews and adjusting designs to address technical constraints while preserving the core experience.\",[197,458,460],{\"id\":459},\"analytics-implementation\",\"Analytics Implementation\",[182,462,463],{},\"We integrated analytics to track our success metrics, setting up dashboards to monitor key interactions and user journeys.\",[197,465,467],{\"id\":466},\"post-launch-iteration\",\"Post-Launch Iteration\",[182,469,470],{},\"After launch, we established a regular cycle of analysis and iteration:\",[225,472,473,476,479],{},[228,474,475],{},\"Weekly reviews of user feedback and behavior data\",[228,477,478],{},\"Bi-weekly design sprints to address emerging issues\",[228,480,481],{},\"Monthly feature planning based on usage patterns\",[189,483,485],{\"id\":484},\"results-learnings\",\"Results & Learnings\",[182,487,488],{},\"Six months after launch, EcoTrack has exceeded our initial success metrics:\",[225,490,491,494,497],{},[228,492,493],{},\"52% increase in daily active usage\",[228,495,496],{},\"78% of users report better understanding of their environmental impact\",[228,498,499],{},\"Average user has adopted 3.4 new sustainable habits\",[182,501,502],{},\"The most valuable lesson from this project was the importance of making abstract concepts tangible. By translating complex environmental data into personal, actionable insights, we created an experience that not only educated users but empowered them to make meaningful changes.\",[189,504,506],{\"id\":505},\"conclusion\",\"Conclusion\",[182,508,509],{},\"Effective product design is never a linear journey—it's a continuous cycle of learning and refinement. By staying focused on user needs while maintaining a flexible approach to problem-solving, we can create products that not only meet business objectives but genuinely improve people's lives.\",[182,511,512],{},\"I'd love to hear about your own design process and how you approach similar challenges. Feel free to reach out with questions or share your experiences in the comments below.\",{\"title\":514,\"searchDepth\":515,\"depth\":515,\"links\":516},\"\",2,[517,523,528,534,539,544,545],{\"id\":191,\"depth\":515,\"text\":192,\"children\":518},[519,521,522],{\"id\":199,\"depth\":520,\"text\":200},3,{\"id\":212,\"depth\":520,\"text\":213},{\"id\":219,\"depth\":520,\"text\":220},{\"id\":239,\"depth\":515,\"text\":240,\"children\":524},[525,526,527],{\"id\":246,\"depth\":520,\"text\":247},{\"id\":253,\"depth\":520,\"text\":254},{\"id\":288,\"depth\":520,\"text\":289},{\"id\":321,\"depth\":515,\"text\":322,\"children\":529},[530,531,532,533],{\"id\":328,\"depth\":520,\"text\":329},{\"id\":335,\"depth\":520,\"text\":336},{\"id\":353,\"depth\":520,\"text\":354},{\"id\":371,\"depth\":520,\"text\":372},{\"id\":389,\"depth\":515,\"text\":390,\"children\":535},[536,537,538],{\"id\":396,\"depth\":520,\"text\":397},{\"id\":417,\"depth\":520,\"text\":418},{\"id\":438,\"depth\":520,\"text\":439},{\"id\":445,\"depth\":515,\"text\":446,\"children\":540},[541,542,543],{\"id\":452,\"depth\":520,\"text\":453},{\"id\":459,\"depth\":520,\"text\":460},{\"id\":466,\"depth\":520,\"text\":467},{\"id\":484,\"depth\":515,\"text\":485},{\"id\":505,\"depth\":515,\"text\":506},\"2025-04-23\",\"A detailed breakdown of my iterative design methodology, from initial research to final handoff, with practical tips for designers at every stage.\",\"md\",\"https://images.pexels.com/photos/1050312/pexels-photo-1050312.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1\",{},8,{\"title\":10,\"description\":547},\"CDWNWgtx3hCIt749zuw2sfgA2mN5rNXUtBLTjjH0nz4\",{\"id\":555,\"title\":18,\"author\":556,\"body\":558,\"date\":600,\"description\":601,\"extension\":548,\"image\":602,\"meta\":603,\"minRead\":604,\"navigation\":139,\"path\":19,\"seo\":605,\"stem\":20,\"__hash__\":606},\"blog/blog/psychology-of-color-in-ui-design.md\",{\"name\":175,\"avatar\":557},{\"src\":177,\"alt\":175},{\"type\":179,\"value\":559,\"toc\":598},[560,563,566,569,572,575,592,595],[182,561,562],{},\"Color is one of the most powerful tools in my design arsenal, yet I find it's often reduced to mere aesthetics or brand guidelines. After conducting a series of A/B tests for the Wavelength music app redesign, I've gathered some fascinating insights about how color psychology directly impacts user behavior.\",[182,564,565],{},\"When we initially launched the app, we used a vibrant purple as our primary action color. The color looked great with our brand palette, but our conversion metrics were underwhelming. On a hunch, I proposed testing different primary colors while keeping all other elements identical.\",[182,567,568],{},\"The results were striking: switching to a specific shade of blue increased our call-to-action conversion by 34%. Even more interesting was how different user segments responded to color variations—younger users engaged more with vibrant tones, while our 35+ demographic showed stronger preference for more subdued colors.\",[182,570,571],{},\"Beyond conversion metrics, I discovered that color significantly affected how users perceived waiting times. By implementing a softer color progression in our loading animations, users reported that the app felt faster, even though the actual loading times remained unchanged.\",[182,573,574],{},\"I've since developed a framework for color decision-making that goes beyond aesthetics:\",[259,576,577,580,583,586,589],{},[228,578,579],{},\"Consider the emotional response you want to evoke\",[228,581,582],{},\"Test color choices with your specific user demographics\",[228,584,585],{},\"Use color to create visual hierarchies that guide users naturally\",[228,587,588],{},\"Consider cultural associations of colors for international audiences\",[228,590,591],{},\"Ensure sufficient contrast for readability and accessibility\",[182,593,594],{},\"The most valuable lesson I've learned is that there are no universal \\\"right\\\" colors—only colors that effectively communicate your message and guide users toward their goals within your specific context.\",[182,596,597],{},\"Next time you're selecting a color palette, think beyond what looks good and consider what your colors are actually saying to your users.\",{\"title\":514,\"searchDepth\":515,\"depth\":515,\"links\":599},[],\"2025-03-15\",\"Exploring how strategic color choices can influence user behavior, evoke emotions, and enhance the overall user experience of digital products.\",\"https://images.pexels.com/photos/40799/paper-colorful-color-loose-40799.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1\",{},5,{\"title\":18,\"description\":601},\"fN5DAgIRMQc3gJh92rH6lK6TjZLKEQivx8hu2JR3VJI\",{\"id\":608,\"title\":14,\"author\":609,\"body\":611,\"date\":650,\"description\":651,\"extension\":548,\"image\":652,\"meta\":653,\"minRead\":654,\"navigation\":139,\"path\":15,\"seo\":655,\"stem\":16,\"__hash__\":656},\"blog/blog/how-i-built-my-own-design-system-from-scratch.md\",{\"name\":175,\"avatar\":610},{\"src\":177,\"alt\":175},{\"type\":179,\"value\":612,\"toc\":648},[613,616,619,622,625,639,642,645],[182,614,615],{},\"After years of starting each project with a blank Figma file, I finally took the plunge and created my own comprehensive design system. The process was both challenging and incredibly rewarding, and I wanted to share my approach for other designers considering the same journey.\",[182,617,618],{},\"I started by auditing five of my recent projects, identifying common patterns and components that appeared across different designs. This revealed inconsistencies in my work that I hadn't noticed before—seven slightly different button styles, inconsistent spacing rules, and text styles that varied without clear purpose.\",[182,620,621],{},\"Rather than creating a rigid system upfront, I built it iteratively through a real client project. For the EcoTrack app, I documented each component as I designed it, creating a living system that evolved with the project's needs.\",[182,623,624],{},\"The core of my system includes:\",[225,626,627,630,633,636],{},[228,628,629],{},\"A flexible color system with semantic naming conventions\",[228,631,632],{},\"Typography scales based on the golden ratio\",[228,634,635],{},\"Component variants with clear usage guidelines\",[228,637,638],{},\"Spacing and layout rules that maintain consistency across devices\",[182,640,641],{},\"The biggest challenge wasn't technical but psychological—learning to trust the system instead of reinventing solutions for each new problem. But the payoff has been enormous: my design process is now 40% faster, client revisions have decreased significantly, and handoff to development is much smoother.\",[182,643,644],{},\"If you're considering building your own system, my advice is to start small with core elements, test them on real projects, and document as you go. A good design system should feel like a trusted collaborator, not a set of restrictions.\",[182,646,647],{},\"I've attached a template of my component documentation method below—feel free to adapt it for your own workflow!\",{\"title\":514,\"searchDepth\":515,\"depth\":515,\"links\":649},[],\"2025-03-05\",\"A practical guide to creating your own design system, from initial audit to implementation, and the lessons learned along the way.\",\"https://images.pexels.com/photos/196644/pexels-photo-196644.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1\",{},6,{\"title\":14,\"description\":651},\"v4KwBTVJ90ic2ZwJ_5bpusUulPf4DMyWsNxXMwW-oUQ\",{\"data\":658,\"body\":659},{},{\"type\":660,\"children\":661},\"root\",[662],{\"type\":663,\"tag\":182,\"props\":664,\"children\":665},\"element\",{},[666],{\"type\":667,\"value\":668},\"text\",\"I specialize in UX/UI design and front-end development. This includes user research, wireframing, interactive prototyping, creating intuitive user interfaces, building responsive websites and web applications (especially with Vue.js/Nuxt.js), and developing design systems. My goal is to create seamless digital experiences from concept to deployment.\",{\"data\":670,\"body\":671},{},{\"type\":660,\"children\":672},[673],{\"type\":663,\"tag\":182,\"props\":674,\"children\":675},{},[676],{\"type\":667,\"value\":677},\"My process is collaborative and iterative, typically involving stages like Discovery & Research, Ideation & Prototyping, User Testing, Visual Design, and close collaboration with development teams during implementation. I tailor the process based on project needs, always focusing on user-centered solutions.\",{\"data\":679,\"body\":680},{},{\"type\":660,\"children\":681},[682],{\"type\":663,\"tag\":182,\"props\":683,\"children\":684},{},[685],{\"type\":667,\"value\":686},\"Absolutely! I enjoy working with startups to help shape their product vision and create user-friendly interfaces from the ground up. I can adapt my process to fit the fast-paced startup environment.\",1772613568039]","statusCode":200,"statusMessage":"","headers":{"content-type":"application/json;charset=utf-8","x-powered-by":"Nuxt"}}